about.title: Acerca de
about.part1: Orfeo NG BY Copyright 2023 Skina Technologies SAS
about.part1.1: Rewritten from its origin by Skina Technologies S.A.S complying with the best software development practices, under a stack of modern technologies that make it completely web friendly and responsive; is a documentary system that offers security and traceability from the production and distribution of documents following the guidelines of Colombian legislation issued by the General Archive of the Nation,
about.part1.2: designed for medium-sized and large companies that have an advanced level of maturity in their documentary processes and are moving towards managing electronic archival documents.
about.part2: Orfeo NG is a Document Management software written by Skina Technologies S.A.S, with state-of-the-art technologies, which meets the requirements of the regulations for the Colombian and Latin American environment. It is prepared to be an SGDEA and complies with a large part of the MOREQ standard.
about.part3: Orfeo NG has been possible thanks to the support of the Orfeolibre team
about.part4: and the development team and document management experts from Skina Technologies

initialNotificationTemplatesVariables: This module allows you to know the variables that the system uses to make a combination of correspondence, which can be used in the trades that are planned. To use one of these variables, what you must do is following:

initialNotificationTemplatesVariablesArr.0: 1. Select the variable (only the name of the variable).
initialNotificationTemplatesVariablesArr.2: 3. Paste the variable in the Word or legal document that is being generated.

initialNotificationTrd: This module allows you to configure the structure of the format used for the construction of the TRDs, that is, it allows you to indicate each of the data used in the creation of the TRD, according to what is stipulated by the general file of the nation AGN, this configuration applies exclusively to loading a format in Excel

textNotificationMasiveTrdUno: In this module the structure of how the TRD format that will be loaded in the system should be read is configured, it is important to clarify that each of the fields of the form, has a description and a location in the TRD, on the other hand, the End days field,
textNotificationMasiveTrdTres: refers to the end days or procedures that documentary types will have by default if this data is not specified, the system will assign 15 days by default, which will be reflected in the filing form.
textNotificationMasiveTrdCuatro: The form below must be filled out bearing in mind how the Excel format of the trd is structured, each text field refers to a column or cell where the data to be read is found once the final TRDS has been loaded. To help fill out the form, each field has a Column or Cell description and what must be entered in the fields is the letter of the column, for example. (A) or letter and row number, example. (A6)

textFormSurvey: From this form you can configure all the questions that will be asked in the satisfaction survey that will be filled out by citizens. Keep in mind that all the questions entered in the form will make a single survey and each question will be evaluated with 4 levels (excellent, good, fair, poor)
textFormTypeFilingText: Through this module you can manage the types of filing, it is important to take into account the following: The field of filing type code refers to how each of the filings that use the entity will be identified, in the configuration it is indicates that this identification must be: (EN, SA, PQRSD)
textFormTypeFilingNumber: Through this module you can manage the types of filing, it is important to take into account the following: The field of filing type code refers to how each of the filings that use the entity will be identified, in the configuration it is indicates that this identification must be: (1, 2, 3)
Días hábiles para el ciudadano responder: Business days for the citizen to respond
textFormGeneralConfiguration: This module allows you to make a general configuration of the entire system in which you must specify the default values that must be taken into account for the correct operation of the system.
textFormFilingLabel: Through this module you will be able to activate / deactivate the fields that you want to be shown on the filing label that is printed, it is important to be clear that this should be done only once, since it affects at a general level
textFormThirdParty: Keep in mind that when a new client is going to be created and the characterization data is filled in, the system will create an external user who will be sent by email to the registered account, so that they can enter the public page of PQRSD and file a request. Important the Characterization Data option only applies to natural persons
Total por tipo comunicación interna: Total by type of internal communication
textFormPhysicalSpace: From this module you can configure the structure of the physical file (topographic structure) that the entity has, this configuration reaches the level of boxes. Each of the sections is explained below: Building Data: In this section the name and location of each of the file types (Management, Central, Historical) will be configured. Storage Data: In this section the topographic structure will be configured, that is, the physical distribution of each of the file types, for this configuration quantities are entered.
textFormPhysicalSpaceView: The Module, shelf and Box fields refer to the quantities that are configured for each one
textFormArchiveFiling: Through this option, a physical location will be assigned to the file where the selected file is included, since it is the document associated with the file that will rest in the assigned location and the system will show that location to make it easier to consult it. Important, the CONSERVATION UNIT field refers to the number of Folder, Aceta, Book or File where the document is going to rest.
